  "caption_en": "Table S8. Mapping of the 21 INAMHI station locations to the ERA5-Land ~9-km grid cells used in this study. The pixel ID is a study-internal identifier built from the unique rounded ERA5-Land mean temperature footprint (2020–2025); stations falling within the same ERA5-Land grid cell receive the same pixel ID and the same temperature time series from the reanalysis. Five grid cells host two stations each (10 of 21 stations affected); eleven cells host a single station. This produces 16 spatially-independent pixels covering the 21-station network. Per-station ERA5-Land trend statistics in Table 2 should therefore be aggregated to these 16 pixels for valid spatial-independence inference (see §4.1 and §5.5).",
